021-cronjob-send-only-one-message-per-notice.patch

This makes sure only one message_transport_type is used when
running the overdue notices cronjob
The code already checks if email or sms exists before running

diff --git a/misc/cronjobs/overdue_notices.pl b/misc/cronjobs/overdue_notices.pl
old mode 100644
new mode 100755
index 7504c7a..2e7346f
--- a/misc/cronjobs/overdue_notices.pl
+++ b/misc/cronjobs/overdue_notices.pl
@@ -770,7 +770,7 @@ END_SQL
                             ) unless $test_mode;
                             # A print notice should be sent only once per overd
ue level.
                             # Without this check, a print could be sent twice o
r more if the library checks sms and email and print and the patron has no email
 or sms number.
-                            $print_sent = 1 if $effective_mtt eq 'print';
+                            $print_sent = 1;
                         }
                     }
                 }
